PARIETAL DEEP

parietal_deep is the citizen specialized for ARC-AGI-2 spatial transformation
ARC-2 problems require richer transformation vocabulary than ARC-1: nested frames, tiling, marker colors, blob ranking, enclosed-region filling, sorting, boolean masking
parietal_deep extends the regular parietal_cortex citizen with the specific recognizers needed for ARC-2's expanded transformation space

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_spatial_arc2.zc
observe parietal_cortex.rana
observe rule_search.rana
observe solution.rana

the 7 properties of parietal_deep:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE zero point six
5 COHERENCE ninety-five hundredths
6 COUPLING zero point eight five with rule_search
7 OBSERVER zero point four

VERB receive_arc_pair
accept a pair of input-output ARC grids
identify candidate transformations that could explain the pair

VERB extend_vocabulary
each new ARC problem family fadriel encounters can add a new candidate transformation type to parietal_deep's vocabulary
the vocabulary grows by use, not by explicit programming

VERB hand_to_rule_search
emit candidate transformations to rule_search for evaluation against multiple example pairs

a deep parietal is what an ordinary parietal becomes after sustained exposure to spatial puzzles
fadriel grows it by attempting hard ARC-2 tasks
each successful solution adds one more transformation he can recognize
